hen the family lands were still growing, and in the sixteenth century are added further properties in South Cornwall (including one near Looe) and elsewhere; these appear in the later documents published here. These rentals and surveys provide much information about Cornish history in general and in particular for local and family historians in Cornwall, for those interested in social and agricultural history, manorial history, place-names and personal names. There is an introduction covering some of the topics illustrated by the surveys, and helping to make the material accessible to non-specialists.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aArundel family. 0aLand tenurevSourcesxHistoryy16th centuryzEnglandzCornwall (County). 0aLand tenurevSourcesxHistoryyTo 1500zEnglandzCornwall (County). 0aManorsvSourcesxHistoryy16th centuryzEnglandzCornwall (County). 0aManorsvSourcesxHistoryyTo 1500zEnglandzCornwall (County). 4aBritish Local History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / Norman Conquest to Late Medieval (1066-1485).2bisacsh1 aFox, H S A, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPadel, O. J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781787447714?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787447714423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787447714/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles